parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic seat belt can cause the belt to stick in the locked position, making it difficult or impossible to exit the vehicle in an emergency, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The driver's side seat belt fails to retract when the door is opened or closed
the belt sticks in the locked position
the seat belt warning indicator flashes on the dashboard
the belt fails to function properly
the belt tightens around the neck or chest

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized shoulder belt can cause the belt to fail to restrain the driver or passenger during a crash, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The motorized shoulder belt fails to operate
the belt fails to move into the safe position
the belt sticks in the forward position
the belt makes a grinding noise
the belt fails to tighten during a panic stop.
